 NDDC  The ex-militant leaders who convened at Yenagoa, Bayelsa State yesterday, also condemned calls for Dokubo’s sack. Spokesman of the group, Kalaiti Jephthah, said as ex-militants and beneficiaries of the amnesty programme, Dokubo has brought his experience to bear on the running of the amnesty office. “Also, Brambaifa’s appointment, as Acting MD of NDDC is a welcome development and well deserved. “He he has done his bit in the Niger Delta as a revered personality in the struggle and he has demonstrated his readiness to serve and we can attest to the visible renaissance after a long stalemate,” he said. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .